data.name: PointLabel4.Text
data.value: - Under the Game audio settings, you have the option of using either the volume level from the file that you are replacing or set a custom volume level with the slider. The loop start and end options are experimental and if you want the game to repeat the music track after it has played once, then tinker with these two loop options. the value has to be in bytes that is less than or equal to the mp3 file's size.

data.name: PointLabel2.Text
data.value: - Select the .XXX audio file that you want to replace from the second box. If you are playing any of the blu ray disc versions of the game, then make sure to replace the audio file from the dev\hdd0\game folder.

data.name: PointLabel1.Text
data.value: - Select the mp3 audio file that you want to encode from the first box. The selected audio file shouldn't have any metadata or cover art attached to it and the bitrate should be 256kbps or below. You can use a tool like Mp3tag to remove metadata or cover art from the mp3 file before selecting it from this app.
